children.subject: Also I've heard people often pair up 188 and 170, in case you haven't taken that yet/are interested in taking it at some point. They seem to complement each other well.

In my opinion, 162 and 170 are more important than either 168 or 186. Of course, both are heavy workload classes so I wouldn't recommend them together. As far as 168 vs 186, its more about your interest than anything. But in my experience with courses I've taken so far, I've come across 186 concepts far more frequently than 168. I find 168 far more niche than 186.

history.content: Or should I hold off on 168, and take it with 162? Only problem is I would ideally take 162 next spring semester, and it seems like 168 isn't offered every semester, so I might be prolonging 168 even more.
history.subject: Would you recommend taking CS168 or CS186 with 170 next semester?
